import React from 'react';
import Navbar from 'react-bootstrap/Navbar'
import { NavLink } from 'react-router-dom';
import Nav from 'react-bootstrap/Nav'

const NavBar = () => {

    return (
        <div >


            <Navbar bg="light" expand="lg">
                <Navbar.Brand href="#home">COVID-19 World Tracker</Navbar.Brand>
                <Navbar.Toggle aria-controls="basic-navbar-nav" />
                <Navbar.Collapse id="basic-navbar-nav">
                    <Nav className="mr-auto">
                        <Nav.Link to="/" href="#home">Create a New Collection</Nav.Link>
                        <Nav.Link href="#link">View all data for selected Country</Nav.Link>
                    </Nav>
                </Navbar.Collapse>
            </Navbar>















            <NavLink
                to="/new">
                Create a New Collection
            </NavLink>

            <NavLink
                to="/countries">
                View all data for selected Country
            </NavLink>

        </div >
    );
}

export default NavBar;
